A term for a [[pun]], one will occasionally come across the word when reading the works of Russian authors. [[Nikolai Gogol]] is especially known for his extensive use of kalemburs in his texts. In 1919 the Russian [[formalist]] Boris Ejchenbaum wrote an article about Gogol's short story [[The_Overcoat|"The Overcoat"]] in which he addresses Gogol's use of ''kalemburs''. The article has become a classic in [[formalism (literature)|literary formalism]].

See also: [[Russian formalism]].

